commit.message:
Update path prepend behavior on request

Check the requested path if the base path already exists, or if a valid
API path exists. If neither are detected, then prepend the appropriate
api prefix based on the given `api_version`.

commit.message:
Test coverage additions and updates

Updates tests where required and adds new tests for expected behavior
with box provider architecture and API versions.

Add architecture support to box providers

Updates the box provider to handle architecture information. The client
has been updated to target the v2 API by default. Some authentication
endpoints are not available in the v2 API so they remain targeted at the
v1 API. For box provider requests, the API version used is based on
architecture information provided. If no architecture information is
included in the request, it will target the v1 API. Otherwise, it will
use the v2 API.

Search has also been updated to properly handle filtering by a specific
architecture.
Use client method for token validation
